  "prompt": "Can Home Depot copy a car key with a chip if I provide them a blank key with a chip?",
  "response": "Home Depot typically offers key copying services for standard keys, including some types of car keys. However, when it comes to car keys with chips (also known as transponder keys), the process can be more complicated. \n\nMost hardware stores, including Home Depot, usually do not have the equipment necessary to program transponder keys. Even if you provide a blank key with a chip, they may not be able to copy or program it. Transponder keys require specific programming to match the vehicle's ignition system, which often needs to be done by a dealership or a specialized locksmith.\n\nIf you need a duplicate transponder key, it is best to contact a locksmith who specializes in automotive keys or visit your vehicle's dealership. They will have the necessary tools and knowledge to duplicate and program the key correctly.",
